  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You exhale, pushing all the air in your lungs forward in the direction of your outstretched hand. Your breath becomes a strong gust that throws objects and creatures around.</em></p><p>Candles, torches, and similar unprotected flames in range of the wind are extinguished.</p><p><strong>Strength Save</strong> </p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Targets are pushed 15 feet away from you in a direction following the line.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Nothing</p></li><li><p><strong>Area Hazard:</strong> Any movement going towards you against the direction of the latest gust of wind counts as movement through &amp;reference[difficultterrain].</p></li><li><p><strong>Concentration:</strong> On each of your subsequent turns, you can use a bonus action to both change the direction of the wind and have the spell occur again.</p></li></ul>",
      "chat": ""
    },
